Text.Value: The goblins were a threat to a group of tieflings nearby. I put an end to that threat.
Never mind that - what are you doing, picking over corpses?
But if you won't tell me, no matter. A truth is second best to the truth.

EditorData.NodeContext: journalistic type who is more interested in a good story than a true story

Text.Value: Best not to hang around. Whoever is responsible for this mess may still be here... unless this was your doing?

EditorData.NodeContext: polite advice on first sentence, and then a warning. The final phrase is a mixture of curiosity and awe

Text.Value: It was self-defence, I had no choice.
Find me at my camp - we can talk there.
Drat. Then I suppose I'll have to stitch together the truth with naught but my own good sense.

EditorData.NodeContext: only a little annoyed - 'stitching together the truth' is a chance to impress, and he's keen to do that

Text.Value: Pick a different brain. I can't help you.
Ah, but you must mean Zevlor and the lot! I spent some time with them myself. Kind, if underfortunate people.

EditorData.NodeContext: pleased - Zevlor (Zev-lore); 'underfortunate' is an intentional nonsense word that he uses pompously to expand his vocabulary

Text.Value: Guilty. I killed them all.
Afraid not.
I did - I poisoned them.
Of course, my friend. But facts belong to no one and everyone. Please: what happened here?

EditorData.NodeContext: inquisitive journalistic type, prodding for answers

Text.Value: My friend! Are you responsible for the slaughter of these goblins?

EditorData.NodeContext: delighted to see us - asking about the slaughter with intense curiosity
EditorData.logicalname: Goblins killed, not poisoned, has met

Text.Value: I have my own reasons.
Guilty as charged.
There! That's the last frothing innard catalogued.

EditorData.NodeContext: investigating dead goblins - pleased to meet the perpetraror of the masscare

Text.Value: Someone must collect the facts and arrange them in a clever order.

EditorData.NodeContext: proud

Text.Value: Hmmm... Your story may be relevant, but the stench of this place is hardly suited to civilised conversation.

EditorData.NodeContext: politely trying to tag along with the players

Text.Value: Volothamp Geddarm, realm-renowned author, auteur, and tastemaker, at your service.

EditorData.NodeContext: arrogance, introducing himself with a flourish

Text.Value: It's no wonder you'd endeavour to help them. Still, it's quite an... quite an impressive cost of goblin life.

EditorData.NodeContext: impressed but shocked by what we've done (killed a lot of goblins)

Text.Value: I did. I killed them all.
Leave.
I'll be no trouble, my friend. Name a location and I'd be happy to meet you there.

EditorData.NodeContext: a polite plea

Text.Value: Just nosing out the facts. Something happened here, and it's my job - my calling - to discover what.

EditorData.NodeContext: arrogant - his 'calling' (at this moment, asking annoying questions) is the most important thing in the world as far as he sees it

Text.Value: I wonder if we might continue this elsewhere. You've a brain I'd like to pick.
Indeed - I poisoned the lot of them.
Why are you still here?
You poor soul. These goblins were spoiling for a fight under the banner of their so-called 'Absolute.'

EditorData.NodeContext: mock sympathy - he's talking to somebody who claimed they massacred an entire camp of goblins in self-defense and is a little doubtful. But the goblins' new god, the Absolute, is intriguing to him and he'd like to follow up on that

Text.Value: You? Why? And how? But wait, wait - let me get a fresh quill. Now. You were saying?

EditorData.NodeContext: preparing to take notes like an inquisitive journalist at a crime scene
EditorData.StateChangeTags: [Volo] is holding a Quill and Notebook

Text.Value: Leave.
There! Last dismembered limb catalogued.

EditorData.NodeContext: investigating dead goblins - pleased to meet the perpetraror of the masscare
EditorData.logicalname: Goblins killed, not poisoned, not met

Text.Value: Yes?

EditorData.NodeContext: polite

Text.Value: Never mind. What are you doing here anyway - looting corpses?
Indeed, the poisoning was my handiwork.
Tell me - did you see what happened here?

EditorData.NodeContext: preparing to take notes like an inquisitive journalist at a crime scene
EditorData.StateChangeTags: [Volo] is holding a Quill and Notebook

Text.Value: My friend! Are you responsible for the state of these unfortunate souls?

EditorData.NodeContext: delighted to see us - asking about the dead goblins (they were poisoned, hence 'frothing innards') with intense curiosity

Text.Value: Smashing! Ta for now, my friend - only for now!

EditorData.NodeContext: delighted to be invited to join the players' camp

Text.Value: Never mind that - what are you doing? Looting corpses?

Synopsis: Volo, a reknowned scholar, has been captured by goblins and is being forced to sing on a stage at their celebratory party following a raid. One goblin has the responsibility of guarding him and engages him in conversation. If the goblins are killed, he investigates the corpses, researching the cause of death.
